Title: Approach to D-dimensional Gross-Neveu model at finite temperature and
  curvature
Authors: S. Kanemura and H.-T. Sato
Comments: 8 pages, Latex, 3 figures
Report-no: OU-HET 226, NBI-HE-95-38
Journal-ref: Mod.Phys.Lett. A11 (1996) 785-794
\\
  We discuss phase structure of chiral symmetry breaking of the $D$-dimensional
($2\leq D\leq3$) Gross-Neveu model at finite temperature, density and constant
curvature. We evaluate the effective potential in a weak background
approximation to thermalize the model as well as in the leading order of the
$1/N$-expansion. A third order critical line is observed similarly to the $D=2$
case.
